# Language Rule

The entire project must be conducted in English. This includes:

## Code

- All variable names, function names, class names, and identifiers must be in English
- All code comments and documentation strings must be in English
- All error messages and log messages must be in English
- All configuration files and their values should use English naming conventions

## Documentation

- All documentation files (README, markdown files, etc.) must be written in English
- All API documentation and code examples must be in English
- All inline code documentation (docstrings, JSDoc comments, etc.) must be in English

## User Interface

- All UI text, labels, buttons, and messages must be in English
- All user-facing error messages and notifications must be in English

## Communication

- All commit messages must be in English
- All code review comments and discussions should be in English
- All project-related communication and documentation should be in English

## Exceptions

- Only exception: string literals that are part of the application's data or content (e.g., user-generated content, external API responses) may be in other languages if required by the application's functionality
